   "source": [
    "# Detector model interface\n",
    "\n",
    "In addition to the neutrino data itself, the IceCube collaboration provides some information about the detector that can be useful to construct simple simulations and fits. For example, the effective area is needed to connect between incident neutrino fluxes and expected number of events in the detector.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "`icecube_tools` also provides an quick interface to loading and working with such information. This is a work in progress and only certain datasets are currently implemented, such as the ones demonstrated below."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "0107c8a5",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2021-12-30T21:20:59.687317Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2021-12-30T21:20:59.686640Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2021-12-30T21:21:01.095480Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2021-12-30T21:21:01.093954Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [

  },

    "## Effective area, angular resolution and energy resolution\n",
    "\n",
    "We can now use the date string to identify certain datasets. Let's say we want to use the effective area and angular resolution from the `20181018` dataset. If you don't already have the dataset downloaded, `icecube_tools` will do this for you automatically."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "8b298380",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2021-12-30T21:21:01.126505Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2021-12-30T21:21:01.125957Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2021-12-30T21:21:01.980238Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2021-12-30T21:21:01.979400Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from icecube_tools.detector.effective_area import EffectiveArea\n",
    "from icecube_tools.detector.energy_resolution import EnergyResolution\n",
    "from icecube_tools.detector.angular_resolution import AngularResolution"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "f5819713",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2021-12-30T21:21:01.984971Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2021-12-30T21:21:01.984426Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2021-12-30T21:21:02.280922Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2021-12-30T21:21:02.281676Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "my_aeff = EffectiveArea.from_dataset(\"20181018\")\n",
    "my_angres = AngularResolution.from_dataset(\"20181018\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "c5d73f2e",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2021-12-30T21:21:02.302062Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2021-12-30T21:21:02.300423Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2021-12-30T21:21:04.108496Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2021-12-30T21:21:04.109226Z"
    }
   },

   "source": [

    "ax.set_ylabel(\"cos(zenith)\")\n",
    "cbar.set_label(\"Aeff [m^2]\")"
   ]

    "\n",
    "We can bring together these properties to make a detector model that can be used for simulations."

  },
